Spring Security Explained Simply

Imagine you have a house with a lock on the door. Only people with the right key can enter.

ğŸ‘‰ Spring Security is like that lock for your web application. It makes sure that only authorized users can access certain pages or data.
ğŸ”¹ Why Do We Need Spring Security?

Without security, anyone can:
âŒ Access admin pages
âŒ Steal user data
âŒ Modify sensitive information

Spring Security prevents these issues by:
âœ… Authenticating users (Checking "Who are you?")
âœ… Authorizing users (Checking "What can you do?")
âœ… Protecting against attacks (like SQL Injection, CSRF, etc.)
ğŸ”¹ How Spring Security Works?
1ï¸âƒ£ Authentication (Login System)

ğŸ”¹ Checks who you are using username & password
ğŸ”¹ If correct, allows access; otherwise, denies

