Spring Data & JPA Explained Simply

Think of Spring Data JPA like ordering food online. ğŸ”ğŸ“±

    JPA (Java Persistence API) is like the menuâ€”it tells you what you can order (database operations).
    Spring Data JPA is like Swiggy/Zomatoâ€”it simplifies the process of ordering food (writing database queries).

ğŸ”¹ What is JPA?

ğŸ‘‰ JPA (Java Persistence API) is a set of rules to interact with a database using Java objects.
Without JPA (Manual SQL Queries)

